claimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view american eagle outfitters  wikipedia american eagle outfitters from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search american eagle outfitters inc type public traded as nyse aeo sp  component industry retail founded   years ago  founder jerry silverman mark silverman headquarters southside works  hot metal street pittsburgh pennsylvania us number of locations  american eagle outfitters  aeries area served worldwide key people jay schottenstein chairman and interim ceo products apparel accessories lingerie personal care footwear revenue us billion fy  operating income us million fy  net income us million fy  total assets us billion fy  total equity us billion fy  number of employees  jan  website american eagle outfitters american eagle outfitters inc is an american clothing and accessories retailer headquartered in the southside works neighborhood of pittsburgh pennsylvania it was founded in  by brothers jerry and mark silverman as a subsidiary of retail ventures inc a company which also owned and operated silvermans menswear the silvermans sold their ownership interests in  to jacob price of knoxville tennessee american eagle outfitters inc is also the parent company of aerie  the brand targets male and female college students although older adults wear the brand with  american eagle outfitters stores and  standalone and  sidebyside aerie stores in  the first american eagle outfitters store opened in twelve oaks mall in novi michigan some of the brands popular products are lowrise jeans polo shirts graphic tshirts sweatpants henley shirts boxers and briefs outerwear and swimwear contents  development  finances and operations  corporate and headquarters  staffing partnership  franchise agreement  logistics  stores and other brands  aerie  martin  osa  kids  international expansion  new american music union  controversies  strike  abercrombie  fitch lawsuits  opstore count  see also  references  external links developmentedit american eagle outfitters green oak village place an american eagle outfitters store in the mall sm aura premier in bonifacio global city metro manila philippines american eagles beginning was with the silverman family which owned and operated silvermans menswear by the mids two of the silverman brothers—from the third generation of silvermans in the family business—were running the family business jerry silverman was the president and ceo while his brother mark silverman served as executive vicepresident and coo the silverman brothers were convinced they needed to diversify their product offerings in order to continue growing their company they also recognized that the addition of new family owned chains would then enable them to operate more than one store in the same mall their first attempt was to open american eagle outfitters in  positioning it as a proprietor of brandname leisure apparel footwear as well as accessories for men and women emphasizing merchandise suited for outdoor sports such as hiking mountain climbing and camping stores were set up in shopping malls and a catalog was established the chain grew for much of the s in  the owners decided to refocus their business on american eagle outfitters selling their other retail chains at that time there were  american eagle outfitters stores in  different states despite the plans for quick growth after the reorganization american eagle outfitters opened only  new stores by  and the company was losing money at this point the schottensteins who had been  owners of the chain since  bought out the founding silverman familys interest this change in leadership resulted in american eagle finding its present niche casual clothing for men and women selling private label clothes when the company began trading on the nasdaq stock exchange in the second quarter of  it had  stores and a healthy cash flowcitation needed with the cash infusion from the ipo the company opened more than  new stores within the next year several new executives joined the company in  and  leading to another change in the target demographiccitation needed over the next five years revenues quintupled to  billion by  ae opened the first canadian store in   as of january   the company operated  aeo brand stores and  standalone and  sidebyside aerie stores located in shopping malls lifestyle centers and street locations in the united states canada mexico hong kong china the united kingdom and internationally the company had  franchised stores operated by franchise partners in  countries on january   thenceo robert hanson stepped down and jay schottenstein became interim ceo finances and operationsedit on march   the company adjusted its accounting of rent expenses and construction allowances after the securities and exchange commission noted that a number of companies had been improperly logging these items due to disappointing product execution in the womens category american eagle posted only a  gain in the  second quarter profits and the stock price dropped corporate and headquartersedit american eagle outfitters headquarters in mid american eagle outfitters moved its headquarters from warrendale pennsylvania to a more urban location at the southside works complex in pittsburgh the cost of the buildings and adjacent property was approximately  million excluding interior finishing and additional construction costs the addresses of the buildings are  hot metal street and  hot metal street with the numbers symbolizing the first store opening in  the facilities of the southside works campus include a private garage a lab store for each brand photo studio and inhouse cafeteria other offices are located in nyc design and production staffing partnershipedit in june  the company signed an exclusive staffing agreement with jbcstyle this agreement encompassed all of american eagle outfitters freelance staffing needs in new york city as well as any outsourced permanent search the company has opted to engage jbcstyles sister company jonathan beth consultants to manage payroll for all corporate hourly employees american eagle outfitters has renewed its agreement with jbcstyle for two subsequent years franchise agreementedit in june  the company signed the franchisee agreement with m h alshaya one of the leading retailers of the middle east the agreement will see the introduction of the first stores outside the north american market with the first two opening in dubai and kuwait on march  and   respectively and a store which opened on october   in kaslik near beirut lebanon another store opening followed in june  in hamra street beirut followed by another store located in beirut city centre hazmiehcitation needed logisticsedit the company maintains distribution centers in hazleton and warrendale in pennsylvania us as well as ottawa kansas us and mississauga ontario canada stores and other brandsedit items are placed on wooden shelving tables or clothes racks the clothes in lowvolume stores are hung on basic black hangers and highervolume stores have wooden hangers there is usually a flat screen television hanging in the back of the store or behind the cash wrap the floors are typically wood or concrete the theme and displays change based on seasonal lines and promotions aerieedit main article aerie american eagle outfitters aerie store in the southside works area of pittsburgh in february  american eagle launched the aerie lingerie subbrand targeting the american  to yearold female demographic segment in addition to lingerie such as a wide variety of bras and other undergarments the aerie line also sells dormwear active apparel loungewear accessories and sleepwear what started as a subbrand quickly became a standalone concept in its own right featuring a complete fitness line called aerie fit the aerie brand is sold in american eagle outfitters stores online through the american eagle web site and in standalone aerie retail stores the first standalone aerie store opened in august  in greenville south carolina and was followed by two more test stores later that year as of december  there are currently  standalone aerie stores in the united states and in canada aerie has started a campaign that focuses on promoting their models’ real bodies this entails their slogan aeriereal and adding to their advertisements that models seen have not been retouched doing this is a way that they have chosen to take a stand against the use of photo manipulation in media iskra lawrence while she models for the lingerie line is also the global role model for the brand martin  osaedit the companys second standalone lifestyle concept launched in  and targeted men and women from  to  years of age it featured cashmere sweaters and casual clothing for an older target audience they also sold products by fred perry rayban adidas onitsuka tiger and hobo international in march  management announced that all  martin  osa stores would be closed after a failed attempt at success in retail markets causing aeo inc to lose up to  million kidsedit in october  american eagle released and launched kids a line of clothing aimed at children from two to ten years of age initially an online only concept aeo opened its first kids store on july   in the mall at robinson in pittsburgh pa and eight others followed that year expansion continued throughout fy kids stores meant to be a fun shopping experience for younger children featured interactive games and activities throughout the stores that children could play with while shopping american eagle outfitters announced on may   that it would sell or close all  of the kids stores by the end of july  robert hanson who became ceo in january  said kids had a loss after taxes of roughly  million on sales of  million in the  fiscal year on august   american eagle outfitters completed the sale of its kids to ezrani  corp a company formed by ezra dabah the former chairman and ceo of the childrens place ezrani renamed the stores to ruum in  international expansionedit american eagle opened its first canadian store in  followed by a store in san juan puerto rico in  aeo opened stores in kuwait riyadh and dubai a store in kaslik near beirut lebanon was opened on october   a store in cairo egypt opened in late  in september  two stores opened in moscow russia its first store in jordan opened in november  in the brandnew taj mall its first store in tokyo japan opened on april   the first store in tel aviv israel opened in february  after the israelibased clothing retailer fox signed a contract with aeo and have expanded to jerusalem israel currently there are also stores in beijing shanghai and hong kong american eagle outfitters opened its first store in the philippines in march  american eagle is also opening stores in mexico the first opened in mexico city at fashion mall perisur on february   and at centro santa fe on june another is scheduled to open in guadalajara later in  at fashion mall galerías guadalajara in  the company financed the rescue and renovation of the jardín edith sánchez ramírez pocket park in mexico city american eagle has also expanded to the united kingdom in november  so far they have stores in westfield london westfield stratford city and bluewater  the westfield london store opened on november   the westfield stratford city store on november   and the bluewater store on november   all uk operations have now been ceased with their uk website closed and all uk stores due to close by the end of july  american eagle outfitters opened its first store in muscat sultanate of oman on october   new american music unionedit american eagle was the primary sponsor of new american music union a music festival at southside works in pittsburgh on august  and   the concert featured gnarls barkley spoon the raconteurs and bob dylan and his band the festival which had been planned as an annual event did not return for a second year because american eagle had moved away from using music as a marketing tool controversiesedit strikeedit in  textile and apparel workers union unite here launched the american vulture backtoschool boycott of american eagle in protest of alleged workers rights violations at the companys canadian distribution contractor national logistics services nls on the  secondquarter conference call ceo james odonnell clarified the american eagles relationship with nls and its effect on business he explained “ we owned nls with the acquisition of braemar back in  and we subsequently sold off nls in  and we are currently a customer of nls we have really no involvement at all with unite here and nls our only involvement with nls is basically as a customer and there have been some allegations made i think to some of to the public about it affecting our business i can tell you right now it has not affected our business ” abercrombie  fitch lawsuitsedit since  abercrombie  fitch has sued american eagle outfitters at least three times for allegedly copying its designs and its advertisements on all occasions american eagle prevailed in court under the statement that af cannot stop american eagle from presenting similar designs since such designs cannot be copyrighted in the united states nevertheless american eagle clothing designs have since trended away in appearance from abercrombie  fitch designs the merchandise offered by american eagle is considered to be retrovintage costefficient clothing whereas abercrombie  fitch merchandise has become an internationally known nearluxury line of clothing with preppy highgrade and highpriced fashions on the same level with that of companies such as the polo ralph lauren company judges have generally ruled that giving abercrombie exclusive rights to market its clothing in a certain way would be anticompetitive hijab controversy in  american eagle outfitters began to sell a jean hijab online which sold out in days the fall marketing also included a muslim model wearing a hijab the reaction was swift some calling it inclusive and progressive and others calling for a boycott of american eagle outfitters opstore countedit africa  egypt   morocco   tanzania  americas  united states   canada   mexico   colombia   puerto rico   panama   peru  asia  israel   japan   china   philippines   united arab emirates   thailand   hong kong   saudi arabia   kuwait   lebanon   singapore   bahrain   indonesia   jordan   qatar   oman  europe  russia   greece  see alsoedit companies portal pittsburgh portal list of companies in the united states list of sp  companies referencesedit  a b c d e f g h american eagle outfitters form k annual report filing date mar   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved january     a b history of american eagle outfitters inc – fundinguniverse fundinguniversecom retrieved on july    a b aeo financeyahoocom retrieved april     namehttpphxcorporateirnetphoenixzhtmlcpirolhistory  httpphxcorporateirnetexternalfileitemugfyzwsuqmzcodqfenoawxksuqmzcmtewffrcgumqt  american eagle company history   news abscbn american eagle outfitters opens first ph store abscbn news retrieved january     karr arnold j january   robert hanson exits american eagle wwd retrieved january     zaccagnini kristen january   american eagle outfitters names jay schottenstein interim ceo market watch by the wall street journal reprinting business wire retrieved january     american eagle to restate results   young vicki m august   american eagle posts  gain in q profits wwd retrieved august     american eagle outfitters  investor relations  press release  american eagle outfitters form k current report filing date may   secdatabasecom retrieved january     american eagle  distribution centers retrieved january     moin david february   american eagle’s strategy for ‘aerie’ intimates wwd  accessdate requires url help  american eagle outfitters introduces new line of dormwear and intimates press release prnewswire august   archived from the original on may   retrieved march   