ed under license direct sales come from the companys websites operations the american eagle outfitters aeo and aerie brands are mostly sold in separate store locations given their contrasting branding aeo sells clothing for young men and women through around  stores and online while aerie sells underwear and intimates for young women through more than  standalone and plus sidebyside stores as well as online american eagle also operates four tailgate clothing co retail stores about  of american eagles revenue comes from aeo womens apparel and accessories and some  comes from mens the companys aerie products bring in the remainder of total sales at around  the majority of american eagles stores are company owned but  are licensed store locations geographic reach products are sold online to  countries worldwide american eagle rings up more than  of its sales in the us canada where the chain has  stores in nine provinces is the companys second largest market the chain also has around  international stores in more than  countries including  stores in mexico six in hong kong  in china and three in the uk sales and marketing the companys merchandise is typically shipped from vendors to us distribution centers in pennsylvania and kansas or its canadian distribution center in ontario it has thirdparty distribution centers in mexico city shanghai the netherlands and hong kong advertising expenditure mostly goes towards direct mail instore photographs and other promotional costs that come with marketing campaigns financial performance in fiscal  revenue grew  to  billion with sluggish  growth in the american eagle outfitters aeo brand complemented by  growth in the smaller aerie brand aeo mens segment decreased in the midsingle digits while womens increased by a similar amount higher average transaction size was partially offset by lower total transaction numbers net income fell  to  million due to an impairment and restructuring charges of  million cash provided by operating activities climbed  to  million due mostly to higher sales strategy american eagles growth strategy includes expanding its store fronts both domestically and internationally in  the chains store opening program eased off it opened a net  stores in the year but it plans to open  american eagle outfitters stores and  aerie stores in  as well as convert  aerie sidebyside format stores meanwhile it plans on closing  american eagle outfitters stores in the same period mergers and acquisitions in  the american eagle acquired iowa based tailgate clothing company which owns and operates tailgate a vintage sportsinspired apparel brand with a college town store concept and todd snyder new york a premium menswear brand for  million the tailgate store concept is an ideal outlet to integrate ae jeans and apparel company background with the exception of aerie american eagle outfitters hasnt had much luck launching new brands its martin  osa sportswear concept for older men and women launched in  was shutdown four years later kids introduced in  as an onlineonly brand and later expanded to  retail locations was sold in mid after disappointing results terms of the kids sale to ezrani  corp which is owned by ezra dabah former ceo of another kids clothing chain the childrens place were not disclosed as a result of the sale american eagle recorded an aftertax loss of about  million which is at the low end of a previously announced range of  million to  million  show less  show full description  show less  show full history  show less  show all competitors aeropostale inc bath  body works llc columbia sportswear company dillards inc guess inc hot topic inc jcrew group inc l l bean inc levi strauss  co macys inc nordstrom inc pacific sunwear of california llc ralph lauren corporation target corporation the gap inc victorias secret direct llc victorias secret stores llc  show less  show all company news and press releases the stock market basically thinks abercrombie  fitch may not be ar